### What was added

**`common/chat.cpp` — new handler function (lines 1519–1544)**

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 format:
    //   [INST] {system}\n\n{user} [/INST] {assistant}</s> [INST] {user} [/INST] …
    // System messages are prepended to the first user turn; there is no dedicated
    // [SYSTEM_PROMPT] wrapper (that belongs to the Ministral 3 / v7 family).
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt           = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format           = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = { "[INST]", "[/INST]" };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**`common/chat.cpp` — auto-detection clause in `common_chat_try_specialized_template` (lines 1717–1725), inserted after GigaChatV3 and before `return std::nullopt`**

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT].
// The Ministral 3 / v7 family uses [SYSTEM_PROMPT] and is already handled above,
// so the absence of [SYSTEM_PROMPT] is the distinguishing criterion here.
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

### Key design decisions

| Aspect | Decision |
|---|---|
| **Detection marker** | `[INST]` + `[/INST]` present, `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent |
| **Ordering** | Appended last, after all existing handlers — Ministral 3 is caught first (it requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`), so there's no collision |
